Based on the given parameter grid and general design principles, I propose the following bold and distinctive recommendation for the optimal concrete formulation:

The formulation is Powderkg = 440, wc = 0.45, materials = 0.7/0.3, curing = heat.

By increasing the powder content to 440 kg/m³, we are maximizing the particle packing and pozzolanic reaction, leading to improved compressive strength. A lower water-to-cement ratio of 0.45 helps to reduce porosity and increase strength. Additionally, a higher ratio of fly-ash to GGBFS at 0.7/0.3 enhances the geopolymerization process. Finally, heat curing accelerates the geopolymerization reaction, resulting in a higher compressive strength.

This unique formulation aims to push the boundaries and achieve even higher compressive strength results. Laboratory testing will provide confirmation of its effectiveness.
